      <item>
        <title>Whonix Installer</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Algernon]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote" data-post="4" data-topic="3938" data-full="true">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/patrick/40/17_1.png" class="avatar"> Patrick:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Why an iso?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Most or all of the time I came into contact with the Debian installer were the isos for installing Debian.<br>
What would “sudo apt-get install whonix-virtualbox” do in the end? Set up a complete host system or just download and import the VM images?<br>
It probably can’t setup the encrypted system as described above. At least not on the system where it is currently running.</p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/whonix-installer/3938/5">Read full topic</a></p>
